    "title": "script: qa: Improve `Key::Fingerprint` type safety",
    "user": {
      "login": "davidgumberg",
      "id": 2257631,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyNTc2MzE=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2257631?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/davidgumberg",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Extracted from pseudoramdom's work in #35436:\r\n\r\nInstead of using vectors for key fingerprints, use `std::array`'s whose length can be reasoned about at compile time.\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\nusing KeyFingerprint = std::array<unsigned char, 4>;\r\n```\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n-    unsigned char vchFingerprint[4];\r\n+    KeyFingerprint fingerprint;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis allows the replacement of a lot of raw `memcpy` + trust-me-bro lengths, with the assignment operator:\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\n-    memcpy(ret.vchFingerprint, vchFingerprint, 4);\r\n+    ret.fingerprint = fingerprint;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis commit also adds two helper functions for\r\n- Retrieving the [fingerprint of a key identifier](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0032.mediawiki#user-content-Key_identifiers) (`CKeyID`)\r\n- Retrieving the fingerprint of the key identifier of an XPUB.",
    "labels": [
